race.comment: DENSETSU (1) resumes. Compared to some of these, he's relatively lightly raced with 14 starts to his name, and his best performances have him firmly in the finish. KAZOTSKY (5) resumes. He wasn't far away when fourth in a stronger race at Corowa last preparation and has to be respected off that. BROMEO (3) has been thereabouts his past two and is in the mix from the good draw. ADELSUN (4) last appeared five-and-a-half weeks ago over 1300m at Dubbo when she finished tenth. This is her first run for the Andrew Dale stable. Expecting a bright start for the new mentor. LITTLE MISS GRACE (6) can improve on recent runs.
